FBIS4-5136 "dreas067_h_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-067 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 Brunei, Malaysia & Singapore Malaysia Thai Helicopter Carrier Purchase No `Threat' Thai Helicopter Carrier Purchase No `Threat' BK0504134894 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in English 1300 GMT 5 Apr 94 BK0504134894 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network English BFN [Text] Malaysia does not consider as a security threat to the country the Royal Thai Navy's plan to purchase a helicopter carrier. This was stated by Chief of Navy Vice Admiral Datuk Sri Mohamed Sharif Ishak. He said any development of the armed forces of the ASEAN countries should not be considered as a threat because it could contribute to regional defense capability. He even revealed that the stronger the forces the better the grouping. He was speaking at a maritime security forum of the Malaysian Institute of Maritime Affairs in Kuala Lumpur. Meanwhile, visiting Rear Admiral Thammanun Nathirot of the Royal Thai Navy said Thailand has no plans to buy an aircraft carrier or an attack warship, but will buy a helicopter carrier to provide support for its sea defense system.
